---
import PortfolioLayout from '../layouts/PortfolioLayout.astro';
import { Image } from '@astrojs/image/components';
import PortfolioHero from '../components/Portfolio/Hero';
import SmallProjectList from '../components/Portfolio/SmallProjectList';

const imageClasses = "max-w-sm rounded-lg shadow-2xl"
const imageWidth = "200"
const imageHeight = "400"
---

<!--
  @astropage
  The landing page accessed by going to `"/"` or by clicking either the logo or the home navigation
  button.
-->

<PortfolioLayout>
  <PortfolioHero reverse={false}>
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-accent text-4xl text-center">Tommy Breslein</h1>
        <h3 class="py-2">Trained in numerical astrophysics</h3>
        <h3 class="py-2">Working as a system admin</h3>
        <h2 class="py-2">Going-to-be software developer</h2>
      </div>
      <Image src="../../assets/portfolio/profile1.jpg" class={imageClasses} alt="" width={imageWidth} height={imageHeight}/>
  </PortfolioHero>

  <PortfolioHero reverse={true}>
      <div>
        <p class="py-2">I may be fairly new, but I do not know anyone as passionate as me when it comes to tech and building software.<br>I love diving into the nitty gritty: Figuring out how to architecture something elegantly to combine extensibility, robustness, and performance; I can spend days on that without ever getting bored.</p>
        <p class="py-2">I am admittedly lazy; in a good way. You will never see me do a task thrice, because I will have automated it in the meantime.</p>
        <p class="py-2">My unique background also allowed me to get a handle on a bunch of technologies: Git, Docker, Ansible, CI with GitLab, Linux administration, slurm, a bunch of programming languages and their respective toolchains, ...</p>
      </div>
      <Image src="../../assets/portfolio/profile1.jpg" class="rounded-lg shadow-2xl" alt="" width={imageWidth} height="100"/>
  </PortfolioHero>

  <div class="hero min-h-screen">
    <div class="hero-content flex-col">
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-center">My big projects</h1>

        <!--
          Turns out this isn't easy to abstract away due to the image prop.
          Maybe I can pass the <Image .../> components as children to the SolidJS components?
        -->
        <div class="card lg:card-side bg-base-300 shadow-xl my-2">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h1 class="card-title">corries</h1>
            <ul>
              <li>Framework to run 1D hydrodynamics simulations</li>
              <li>Ultimately aimed at astrophysics simulations</li>
              <li>Blazingly fast âš¡ðŸ¦€</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="card-actions justify-end">
              <a href="https://github.com/tbreslein/corries" target="_blank">
                <button class="btn btn-primary">GitHub Repo</button>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <Image src="../../assets/portfolio/corries.png" alt="" class={imageClasses} aspectRatio="4:3" width="1280"/>
        </div>

        <div class="card lg:card-side bg-base-300 shadow-xl my-2">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h1 class="card-title">tdos</h1>
            <ul>
              <li>My current obsession: Learning how to write a kernel</li>
              <li>I was always interested in how an OS works under the hood, so why not build one?</li>
              <li>Still super early, but I'm also super pumped to build it!</li>
              <li>Follows this guide: <a href="https://os.phil-opp.com/" target="_blank">'Writing an OS in Rust'</a></li>
            </ul>
            <div class="card-actions justify-end">
              <a href="https://github.com/tbreslein/tdos" target="_blank">
                <button class="btn btn-primary">GitHub Repo</button>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <Image src="../../assets/portfolio/corries.png" alt="" class="max-w-sm rounded-lg shadow-2xl" aspectRatio="4:3" width="1280"/>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <SmallProjectList />

  <PortfolioHero reverse={false}>
      <div>
        <h1>If you are looking to hire me, this is what you can expect:</h1>
        <p>In me you will find someone who's extremely inquisitive, results-oriented, and passionate.</p>
        <p>Due to my almost one-of-a-kind profile and history, I have seen sides of software dev world many haven't, and thus I will bring an incredibly unique perspective to your team <em>guaranteed</em>.</p>
      </div>
  </PortfolioHero>
</PortfolioLayout>
